ts unique features and remarkable regional variations within itself. They include the emergence and development of a secondary H tone, postlexical deletion of the primary H tone, and the L boundary tone in question and vocative intonation. These phenomena bear crucially on general issues in prosody, including postlexical tonal neutralizations, competitions between lexical and postlexical tones, and the number of tones that a syllable can maximally bear. The book thus demonstrates the relevance of studying an endangered language/dialect in general linguistic contexts.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEndangered languageszJapanzKoshiki Islands. 0aJapanese languagexDialects. 0aJapanese languagexVersification. 4aBedrohte Sprache. 4aKoshikijima. 4aProsodie. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Phonetics & Phonology.2bisacsh  aEndangered Language.  aKoshikijima Japanese.  aSentence Prosody.  aWord Prosody.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton eBook Package 2023z978311120579308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2022 Englishz978311099370708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2022z9783110993684oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831107301280 cprintz978311073505540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311073007440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110730074423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110730074/original  a978-3-11-099370-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistic